[title] weird bitget cancelorders issue
[issue]
- ccxt version: latest commit
hello , me again;

after i've reported an issue with implicit api endpoint , you fixed it but i still can't get the correct output.

```js
async function bitgettestcancelorders () {
    const allcancelled = await bitget.cancelorders(['954855266430111745','954855913896431617'],'btc/usdt:usdt',{'margincoin':'usdt'})
    return allcancelled
}
```
the error i get is ;
```js
exchangeerror: bitget {"code":"40017","msg":"null 不能为空","requesttime":1663589057925,"data":null}
```
[issue_comments] "hello again @karahancodes, ok we will try to reproduce it on our side, thanks for letting us know", "@karahancodes can you please try again now?", "@carlosmiei  i still get the
**exchangeerror: bitget {"code":"40017","msg":"null 不能为空","requesttime":1663670845910,"data":null}** unfortunately even after pulling the latest commit", "my bad , updated to the latest commit and it works flawlessly , thank you very much !"

[title] \exchange::network_id_to_code(): argument #1 ($networkid) must be of type string, null given, called in /home/cssoftdemo/public_html/vendor/ccxt/ccxt/php/kucoin.php on line 3332
[issue]
### operating system

windows

### programming languages

php

### ccxt version

4.3.13

### description

getting this error while using the withdraw function
[2024-05-06 14:38:55] local.info: ccxt\exchange::network_id_to_code(): argument #1 ($networkid) must be of type string, null given, called in /home/cssoftdemo/public_html/vendor/ccxt/ccxt/php/kucoin.php on line 3332
[2024-05-06 14:40:16] local.error: kucoin unknown error: 28 resolving timed out after 10000 milliseconds {"userid":1,"exception":"[object] (ccxt\\networkerror(code: 0): kucoin unknown error: 28 resolving timed out after 10000 milliseconds at /home/cssoftdemo/public_html/vendor/ccxt/ccxt/php/exchange.php:1618)
[stacktrace]

### code

  if (isset($transfer_process['id'])) {

$params = array();
                        if (isset($request->chain)) {
                            $params['network'] = $request->chain;
                        }

                        try {
                            $provider_withdraw = $this->api->withdraw($request->symbol, $request->amount, $request->recieving_address, $request->memo, $params);
                        } catch (\throwable $th) {
                            return $this->handlewithdrawalerror($user, $request, $wallet, $th->getmessage());
                        }

                        if (isset($provider_withdraw['id'])) {
                            try {
                                $withdraw_id = collect($this->api->fetch_withdrawals())->where('id', $provider_withdraw['id'])->first();
                                $withdraw->trx_id = $provider_withdraw['id'];
                                $withdraw->fee = ($request->amount * $fee) + $withdraw_id['fee']['cost'];
                            } catch (\throwable $th) {

                                $withdraw->fee = $fee;
                            }
                        }
                    }
[issue_comments] "the withdraw goes through but we recieve this error sometimes nothing happens", "@shahwaizjerrax it seems php throws error when the parameter type is not correct. we'll fix this asap."
